23/01/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- On Wednesday (22 January), government spokesman Christos Protopappas said Greece would only offer its military facilities for use in an operation against Iraq if there is a resolution by the UN Security Council. He added that war is not inevitable and that Greece would welcome any other means of resolving the conflict. Meanwhile, Foreign Minister George Papandreou launched an initiative for the EU to adopt a common stance on Iraq. On Wednesday, he spoke by phone with his counterparts in France, Portugal and Austria. (Athens News Agency, Macedonian Press Agency - 22/01/03)
